cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of co-teaching, a method developed for handling noisy labels in classification problems, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of automatic labelling methods, which can introduce noise to the labels, and the need to mitigate the effects of this noise, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL) and cryptography (cs.CR).
